**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

There are actually two separate sub‐structures:

1) **Left “Tower” Structure (7 blocks total)**
   - **Base/Columns:** Three orange cylinders (#9). Two stand side by side at the bottom; the third is stacked atop one of those to form a taller column.  
   - **Bridging Block:** A single horizontal yellow rectangular prism (#7) laid across the top(s) of the two columns.  
   - **Red Arch:** A red arch block (#1) centered on the yellow prism.  
   - **Half‐Cylinder Insert:** A yellow half‐cylinder (#10) fitting under the red arch.  
   - **Orange Wedge Roof:** One orange wedge (#13) perched on top (giving the “roof” shape).

2) **Right “Framed” Structure (6 blocks total)**  
   - **Top & Bottom Rails:** Two horizontal yellow rectangular prisms (#7)—one at the bottom, one at the top.  
   - **Four Cubes Between Rails:**  
     • Green cube (#4), upper‐left  
     • Orange cube (#5), lower‐left  
     • Blue cube (#3), upper‐right  
     • Red cube (#6), lower‐right  

Hence there are 13 blocks in all, arranged in two layers on the right structure and four layers on the left.

---

**Blocks Needed From the Dictionary (with exact orientations)**

• #9 (Orange cylinder) × 3  
• #7 (Yellow rectangular prism, horizontal) × 3  
• #1 (Red arch) × 1  
• #10 (Yellow half‐cylinder) × 1  
• #13 (Orange wedge) × 1  
• #4 (Green cube) × 1  
• #5 (Orange cube) × 1  
• #3 (Blue cube) × 1  
• #6 (Red cube) × 1  

---

**Assembly Order**

Use the following step‐by‐step (you can of course group the two sub‐structures, but here is one possible sequence):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 9  
  Step2: Move block with index 9  
  Step3: Move block with index 9  
  Step4: Move block with index 7  
  Step5: Move block with index 1  
  Step6: Move block with index 10  
  Step7: Move block with index 13  
  Step8: Move block with index 7  
  Step9: Move block with index 5  
  Step10: Move block with index 6  
  Step11: Move block with index 4  
  Step12: Move block with index 3  
  Step13: Move block with index 7
}
